Package: d3geoviz
Type: Package
Title: SVG interactive maps (d3 ecosystem)
Version: 0.7.11
Authors@R: person("Nicolas", "Lambert", email = "nicolas.lambert@cnrs.fr", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Nicolas Lambert <nicolas.lambert@cnrs.fr>
Description: `d3geoviz` is an R package for thematic mapping. As its name suggests, it's an htmlwidget based on the [d3.js](https://d3js.org/) ecosystem ported by Mike Bostock. More specifically, it is an implementation of the [geoviz](https://riatelab.github.io/geoviz/) JavaScript library developed by [RiateLab](https://riate.cnrs.fr/riatelab.html). The package can be used to create a wide range of interactive, zoomable vector maps, taking advantage of d3's many features: proprtional symbols, pictograms, typologies, choropleth maps, Spikes, tiles, Droing cartograms, etc. 
